'''Robert <U+201C>Bob<U+201D> Guy Walls''' (7 February 1927 <U+2013> 11 November 1999) was a painter born in Upper Hutt, New Zealand.<ref>Evening Post, 3 October 1968</ref>

After finishing his education at [[Wellington College]], Walls worked for the Union Steamship Company.<ref>Evening Post. Kiwi helps care for antiquities. Wednesday 16 November 1988</ref>  He spent 17 years (1943 to 1960) employed by the shipping company, including 12 years at sea as a purser on ships trading mainly between New Zealand and Canada,<ref>Upper Hutt Leader, U.H born artist makes name in Britain</ref><ref>An exhibition of recent paintings by Tony Lewis and Robert Walls. The MacGregor Wright Gallery, Wellington. 1993</ref> and as shipping representative in Tonga and the Cook Islands.<ref>Horton-Fawkes N. Edgar Mansfield, Sculptures; Robert Walls, Paintings.</ref><ref>An exhibition of recent paintings by Sylvia Riley and Robert Walls. The MacGregor Wright Gallery, Wellington. 1989</ref>  It was during this time that he began painting as a hobby.<ref>Evening Post. Kiwi helps care for antiquities. Wednesday 16 November 1988</ref>

Walls arrived in London in 1960, and subsequently studied at the [[Chelsea School of Art]] (1960<U+2013>1963).<ref>Evening Post, 3 October 1968</ref><ref>Evening Post. Kiwi helps care for antiquities. Wednesday 16 November 1988</ref><ref>Wadia B. Robert Walls. The Arts Review. Drian Galleries. 1965</ref>  His first solo exhibition was in 1964 at the Drian Galleries in London.<ref>Upper Hutt Leader, U.H born artist makes name in Britain</ref><ref>Horton-Fawkes N. Edgar Mansfield, Sculptures; Robert Walls, Paintings.</ref>  He painted full-time for many years, along with some lecturing and teaching.<ref>An exhibition of recent paintings by Sylvia Riley and Robert Walls. The MacGregor Wright Gallery, Wellington. 1989</ref>

By the 1970s Walls was finally obliged to obtain employment to ease the insecurity of living off an artist<U+2019>s income.<ref>Nelson Evening Mail. Exhibition by NZ artist. 2 February 1989</ref>  He worked briefly at the Foreign Office, and then at the British Museum.  Here, he worked as a curator until 1992 in the Prehistoric and Romano-British Departments,<ref>Evening Post. Kiwi helps care for antiquities. Wednesday 16 November 1988</ref><ref>An exhibition of recent paintings by Tony Lewis and Robert Walls. The MacGregor Wright Gallery, Wellington. 1993</ref><ref>An exhibition of recent paintings by Trevor Hayter and Robert Walls. The MacGregor Wright Gallery, Wellington. 1996</ref> among other things being involved with arrangements for the famous [[Lindow Man]] and in displaying the [[Vindolanda Tablets]], the earliest written materials yet found in Britain.<ref>An exhibition of recent paintings by Sylvia Riley and Robert Walls. The MacGregor Wright Gallery, Wellington. 1989</ref><ref>Nelson Evening Mail. Exhibition by NZ artist. 2 February 1989</ref>  Walls held many exhibitions in Europe, the United Kingdom and New Zealand, and his works are in numerous collections both public and private, including those of the Contemporary Art Society and the New Zealand National Gallery.<ref>An exhibition of recent paintings by Sylvia Riley and Robert Walls. The MacGregor Wright Gallery, Wellington. 1989</ref>

==Painting==
Walls painted using various media, including oils, water colour and pastels, and gouache.  His works are typically of land, sea and townscapes, the landscapes being mainly those of Yorkshire, Scotland, Spain and New Zealand.<ref>Upper Hutt Leader, U.H born artist makes name in Britain</ref><ref>Nelson Evening Mail. Exhibition by NZ artist. 2 February 1989</ref><ref>''New Zealand Women<U+2019>s Weekly''. New Zealander holds second one-man-show. 28 March 1966, page 20</ref>

==Personal life==
Walls lived much of his adult life in London, with his partner John McLeod.

